  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 13 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 3 critical, 20 high, 7 medium, 9 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR); plus 20 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI). Network hotspots: Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Bacău George Enescu (BCM/LRBC), Haugesund Airport, Karmøy (HAU/ENHD), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Stockholm Skavsta (NYO/ESKN) and 8 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, approach minima limits and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Bacău George Enescu (BCM/LRBC), Haugesund Airport, Karmøy (HAU/ENHD) and 9 others.",
  "detail90": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 13 airports right now. Base airports (focus): London Luton (LTN/EGGW) — HIGH: strong gusts risk; cloud base around 100 ft | London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) — HIGH: cloud base around 400 ft | Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) — HIGH: mist; strong gusts risk; cloud base around 500 ft | Sibiu (SBZ/LRSB) — HIGH: thunderstorm / convective risk | Timişoara Traian Vuia (TSR/LRTR) — HIGH: fog; strong gusts risk; visibility down to 600 m, cloud base around 200 ft | Iaşi (IAS/LRIA) — CRIT: fog; visibility down to 200 m, RVR down to 400 m, cloud base around 100 ft; below approach minima (current METAR) and 17 others. Worst affected now: Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH) — CRIT: fog; visibility down to 150 m, cloud base around 200 ft; below approach minima (current METAR) (drivers: low-visibility takeoff restrictions, runway visual range (RVR) constraints, approach minima limits) | Bacău George Enescu (BCM/LRBC) — CRIT: freezing fog; runway contamination risk; visibility down to 150 m, RVR down to 175 m, cloud base around 100 ft (drivers: low-visibility procedures (reduced capacity), runway visual range (RVR) constraints, approach minima limits) | Haugesund Airport, Karmøy (HAU/ENHD) — CRIT: fog; visibility down to 350 m, cloud base around 0 ft; below approach minima (current METAR) (drivers: approach minima limits, very low visibility, low ceilings) | Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) — CRIT: fog; snow; visibility down to 800 m, cloud base around 100 ft (drivers: very low visibility, low ceilings, thunderstorm/convective risk) | Stockholm Skavsta (NYO/ESKN) — CRIT: mist; snow; cold-temperature performance penalties (drivers: approach minima limits, cold-temperature performance penalties, low ceilings) | Stockholm-Arlanda (ARN/ESSA) — CRIT: snow; cold-temperature performance penalties; visibility down to 2.5 km, cloud base around 400 ft (drivers: cold-temperature performance penalties, low ceilings, snow/blowing snow) and 7 other